But I don't expect such a change," he noted.
Debts are growing
The public debt stems from the debt of the state government and comes mainly from the accumulation of deficits of the state budget.
The sovereign debt is financed by treasury bills, government bonds, direct bonds or, for example, bonds issued by the European Investment Bank.
Meanwhile, domestic public debt rose to 719.4 billion crowns this year.
Meanwhile, the state's foreign debt rose by 1.7 billion crowns to 123.3 billion.
The so-called marketable public debt reached 803.3 billion crowns at the end of September and fell by 13.7 billion since June.
The average maturity of government debt rose to 6.5 years.
"Total debt increased by 13 percent over the year from the first to the third quarter, which is really a lot considering how well the economy is doing.
