The Congress approves the MIFID directive, which came into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary draft, which ended today with the congressional resolution in the Senate on the additional/absent amendments associated with the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing both regulations to enter into force by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the members of Congress and the Senate, who had pursued in their negotiations and votes the goal of establishing the best possible regulation that ensures the safety of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market activity.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, MIFID, which redefines the Investment Services Regulation, aims to improve investor protection, increase the control rights of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promote cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive makes it possible to provide financial advice to specialised firms as well as to natural or legal persons and also contributes to the creation of new Financial Services Companies (ESIS), the advisory firms that merge with investment and brokerage companies in securities.
It also expands the number of systems for executing financial transactions, so that multilateral securities systems and systems for internationalisation of orders to trade are added to regulated circulation markets, which would eventually compete with current economic players.
The law obliges investment companies to communicate on the market the focal points of their company profile, confrontation and ways of dealing with risks and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV's supervisory task.
The Economic Commission of the Congress provided for further changes in retrospect, whereby the decision that the bonded bond must now be regarded as complex financial resources due to its high level of risk for the investor has been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the directive was used to legally limit the areas of work of qualified economists; 30 years after 1977, the regulation restricting the areas of work reserved for economists was issued.
