Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible claim caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding severance payment in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance, which is made up of several factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accidents, higher premiums are due.
For this reason, both over-25s and women have to pay fewer contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When drawing up the premium, the insurance companies must take into account a whole series of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
At this point, we list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance-oriented, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance, such as the lack of driving experience and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best to take out fully comprehensive insurance for ideal insurance coverage, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a fully comprehensive insurance with excess, so that the benefits of a fully comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures customers against external accidental damage, but not against damage caused to their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate with the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty implies an increase in the said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depend on the company and its earnings.
If the company has had a profitable year, it can afford to increase bonus payments, explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract. The reason for this is the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving experience.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a fully comprehensive insurance with deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the beginner has been discarded.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out fully comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person in question allows it.
On the part of insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and their premium payments are correspondingly low.
In this case, a fully comprehensive insurance with excess (with an amount around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which only starts for the third year of the vehicle.
Overall, they drive more relaxed and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible (at an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it must be said that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it involves high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
