The Scottish National Health Service needs to improve criminal record checks for workers from outside Europe, a member of the watchdog said. outside
Chief Financial Controller Robert Black's recommendation came after a foreign doctor was linked to the attack on Glasgow airport in Scotland in June.
Black also expressed concern that the Scottish National Health Service had no precise idea of the number of its foreign staff.
But his report pointed out that other important controls were carried out correctly on a sample of five health authorities.
